title: Honoring the Falconer Girls Volleyball Team upon the occasion of its designation for special recognition
fulltext:
LEGISLATIVE  RESOLUTION  honoring  the Falconer Central High School Lady
Golden Falcons Girls Volleyball Team upon the occasion  of  winning  the
New York State Public High School Athletic Association Class C Champion-
ship

WHEREAS,  It  is  the  intent  of this Legislative Body to recognize and
honor outstanding high school athletic teams  that  have  exhibited  the
teamwork, commitment and drive to succeed in statewide athletic competi-
tions in this great Empire State; and
  WHEREAS,  The  Falconer  Central High School Lady Golden Falcons Girls
Volleyball Team has achieved the first New York State Public High School
Athletic Association Class C title in Falconer history with its win over
Voorheesville Central High School on November 21, 2010; and
  WHEREAS, This talented group of young athletes embodies the true spir-
it of teamwork in achieving a goal, all while demonstrating the  ability
to balance the commitments of academics, family and athletics; and
  WHEREAS,  Recognizing  the heart, desire, team chemistry and capabili-
ties of this team, Coach Darin Kennedy encouraged this group of talented
players as they made their dreams of a state championship come true; and
  WHEREAS, The Lady Golden Falcons Volleyball Team relentlessly  pursued
victory  in  interscholastic  play  throughout  the  regular  season and
beyond, winning the school volleyball  program's  first-ever  Section  6
sectional title; and
  WHEREAS, In the Class C state championship game against Voorheesville,
the  Falconer  Lady  Golden  Falcons played as a cohesive unit and main-
tained a positive attitude throughout the  game,  helping  the  team  to
succeed in achieving the state title; and
  WHEREAS,  This  special group of ambitious and dedicated athletes were
honored with a parade in recognition of their state win, which became  a
shared victory for the students, the school, the alumni and the communi-
ty; and
  WHEREAS,  The Falconer Central High School Lady Golden Falcons Volley-
ball Team ended its season with an overall record of  25-8,  culminating
in the state championship title; now, therefore, be it
  RESOLVED,  That  this  Legislative  Body pause in its deliberations to
congratulate the Falconer Central High School Lady Golden Falcons  Girls
Volleyball  Team on its New York State Public High School Athletic Asso-
ciation Class C championship; and be it further
  RESOLVED, That copies of this Resolution, suitably engrossed, be tran-
smitted to the Falconer Central High School Lady  Golden  Falcons  Girls
Volleyball Team, and to Coach Darin Kennedy.
